{
  "name": "Declare Fate",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/fate.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Fate sphere, caster level 15th.</p>\n<p>You may spend two spell points to place a word on a creature to peer into its near future. Each round, at the end of the creature&#8217;s turn, the creature must succeed at a Will saving throw or be forced to declare all actions that it will take on its next turn and be unable to change them. If a declared action would become impossible to perform (such as casting a spell on a creature that is no longer within range), that action is lost. You are aware of what actions an affected creature intends to take.</p>\n<p>This effect lasts as long as you concentrate, but you may always spend a spell point to allow the effect to endure for 1 minute per caster level without concentration.</p>\n<p><strong>Author's Note:</strong> This does not affect attacks of opportunity, which are normally free actions.</p>\n",
